                    </div>
                    <span>I don't know whether the style of this book is good or not but for me the chapter on generating functions was very readable. At the time of reading I already have read several books for the understanding of generating functions; including Graham, Knuth, and Patashnik's "Concrete Mathematics," which is definitely great but difficult to me. I've got a solid understanding of the subject through two books: Polya et al's "Notes on Introductory Combinatorics" and Sedgewick and Flajolet's.</span>
                  
              
